OL,3,CCut PFAS chemicals in Jersey mains
OL,4,Cwater within five years, experts say
OL,6,FPanel chair, Dr Steve Hajioff, adds:
OL,7,F"PFAS levels in drinking water are
OL,8,Falready lower in Jersey than in many
OL,9,Fplaces around the world, including
OL,10,FLondon and other parts of the UK.
OL,12,F"We have recommended a level of 4ng/L
OL,13,Fin order to future-proof the Jersey
OL,14,Fdrinking water supply.
OL,16,F"It will take time to bring the Jersey
OL,17,Fwater supply in line with our
OL,18,Frecommended new standard, and there is
OL,19,Fno cause for concern in the interim."
